<!-- begin symposium abstract popup -->
<div style="display:none" id="dialog-2253-48" title="Abstract">
<strong>Software for Exascale Computing</strong><br />
<br />
This minisymposium in centered around the German Priority Programme 'Software for Exascale Computing' (SPPEXA). SPPEXA addresses fundamental research on the various aspects of HPC software, which is particularly
urgent against the background that we are currently entering the era of ubiquitous massive parallelism. It drives research towards extreme-scale computing in six areas or research directions: computational algorithms,
system software, application software, data management and exploration, programming, and software tools.
</div>
<!-- end symposium abstract popup -->

