CSM-08 Fluid Structure Interaction Simulations of the Human Heart
Presenter:
Dimosthenis Pasadakis (Università della Svizzera italiana, Switzerland)
Track(s):
Computer Science & Applied Mathematics
+ Abstract
+ Presentation
The human heart presents a challenge to numerical simulations, as it is a complex geometry and it includes deformable soft tissues. We address this challenge by presenting a Fluid-Structure interaction (FSI) approach, based on the immersed boundary (IB) method. Moreover, a semi-automatic procedure to get hybrid three dimensional heart meshes (structured for the fluid, unstructured for the soft tissue), based on the segmentation of patient specific data obtained by computed tomography (CT) scans, is presented.
