Computer Science & Applied Mathematics
+ Abstract
+ Presentation
Neural networks trained on big datasets are usually large graphs that take up too much memory and are thus not suited for mobile devices. Recently various methods to reduce the size of these graphs have emerged which proves that this is problem is of interest for the community. The aim of this project is to develop a novel method to reduce the size of these large graphs by letting the network decide which nodes it finds most important for computation and removing the rest. Special type of neural networks called highway networks will be pruned as they allow us to find which nodes are being used most for computation for a particular input.
