	</script></div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="btn btn-primary btn-extra-small show-abstract" title="Abstract">+ Abstract</a> <div class="abstract hidden"> Recent advances in DNA sequencing technologies significantly changed our understanding of genomic content of living organisms and their evolution. The talk will give a brief overview of current state-of-the-art software tools used for raw DNA sequence processing, genome assembly, single-nucleotide polymorphism detection, filtering and further analyses. The software tools are usually memory-bound and have highly variable resource requirements, are often written in higher-level languages while much less in C or C++. Only a handful use MPI or threads at the best. The talk will show several examples of CPU- or memory-hungry applications. The last part of the talk will give a brief description about the technology for remote execution of the before mentioned bioinformatics tools on a supercomputer infrastructure directly from the user interface of the client application without the necessity to connect directly to the HPC cluster and manage the jobs from the command line interface. </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="submission item" data-id="msa118"> <div class="item-warp"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td"> <div class="time">14:30 - 15:00</div> </div> <div class="td"> <div class="submission-body"> <script class="pasc-abstract-item-json" type="text/template">
