	</script><div class="title">Machine Learning for Chemogenomics on HPC: Progress in the ExCAPE Project</div> <div class="table author-items submission-introduction"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td td-label">Presenter:</div> <div class="td"> <div class="authors inline"> <div class="author"> Tom Vander Aa (IMEC, Belgium)</span> <script class="pasc-biography-item-json" type="text/template">
		{"id":"msa118","title":"Dr.","bio":"","first_name":"Tom","last_name":"Vander Aa","affiliation":"IMEC","country":"Belgium","is_presenter":"1"}
	</script></div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="btn btn-primary btn-extra-small show-abstract" title="Abstract">+ Abstract</a> <div class="abstract hidden"> The ExCAPE project is a Horizon 2020 FET-HPC project to advance the state of the art of machine learning implementations on HPC hardware. We have adopted bioactivity predictions for chemogenomics as a challenging use-case to drive development. In this presentation we will give an overview of the project and lessons learned so far from the algorithm development, data preparation and implementation of scalable software. We will touch on deep learning, and matrix factorization, the use of sparse matrices in those algorithms, load-balancing, and tasking, data set characteristics, HPC implementation challenges and solvers used for machine learning. </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="session-head simple"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td"> <div class="collapse-text"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td time"> <span>15:00 - 15:30</span> </div> <div class="td title"> <span><strong>Coffee Break</strong>, Foyer</span> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="td icon"> <div class="collapse-icon"> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="session-head simple"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td"> <div class="collapse-text"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td time"> <span>15:30 - 17:30</span> </div> <div class="td title"> <span><strong>Minisymposia and Papers Sessions</strong></span> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="td icon"> <div class="collapse-icon"> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="session-head submission" id="collapse-sess236-head"> <a href="#collapse-sess236" data-toggle="collapse" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseExample"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td"> <div class="collapse-text"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td time"> </div> <div class="td title"> <span><strong>AP02 ACM PASC17 Papers Session II</strong>, Room A</span> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="td icon"> <div class="collapse-icon"> <div class="spotws-svg arrow-right"> <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" id="Ebene_1" x="0px" y="0px" width="48px" height="48px" viewBox="0 0 48 48" style="enable-background:new 0 0 48 48;" xml:space="preserve" class="spot-svg spot-svg-arrow-right"> <g id="Page-1"> <g id="arrow-left"> <polygon id="Shape-Copy-3" points="20.1,33.2 19,32.1 27.8,23.6 19,15.1 20.1,14 30,23.6 "/> </g> </g> </svg> </div> <div class="spotws-svg arrow-down" style="display: none;"> <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" width="48px" height="48px" viewBox="0 0 48 48" version="1.1" class="spot-svg spot-svg-arrow-down"> <g id="Page-1" stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd"> <g id="arrow-down" fill="#000000"> <polygon id="Shape" points="14.9042553 19.7178256 15.9574468 18.6646341 24.5 27.4412299 33.0425532 18.6646341 34.0957447 19.7178256 24.5 29.6646341"/> </g> </g> </svg> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </a> </div> <div class="collapse" id="collapse-sess236"> <div class="session-body"> <div class="session-introduction"> <div class="table session-introduction"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td td-label">Chair:</div> <div class="td"> <div class="chairs inline"> <div class="author"> Jack Wells (Oak Ridge National Laboratory, United States of America)</span> <script class="pasc-biography-item-json" type="text/template">
		{"id":"1457","bio":"","first_name":"Jack","last_name":"Wells","affiliation":"Oak Ridge National Laboratory","country":"United States of America","type":"Session Chair"}
