	</script><div class="title">GeoPC: Composable Solvers for Geophysics on Modern Architectures</div> <div class="table author-items submission-introduction"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td td-label">Presenter:</div> <div class="td"> <div class="authors inline"> <div class="author"> Patrick Sanan (Università della Svizzera italiana, Switzerland)</span> <script class="pasc-biography-item-json" type="text/template">
		{"id":"msa287","title":"Dr.","bio":"","first_name":"Patrick","last_name":"Sanan","affiliation":"Universit\u00e0 della Svizzera italiana","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"1"}
	</script></div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="btn btn-primary btn-extra-small show-abstract" title="Abstract">+ Abstract</a> <div class="abstract hidden"> We describe recent work within the GeoPC PASC project, synthesizing software components into a geophysical application. This work demonstrates the incorporation of several modern computational components into the application code pTatin3D for lithospheric dynamics. Our focus is to run realistic simulations at high efficiency on the Piz Daint supercomputer, leveraging its hybrid compute nodes to solve the nonlinear Stokes equations with complex rheologies. Components discussed include pipelined (communication-hiding) Krylov methods, processor agglomeration via a reusable component, GPU-enabled subsolves, and GPU-accelerated multigrid smoothing. We share our lessons learned as a result of undertaking an ambitious co-design project, and current practical results within a high-resolution rifting simulation will be discussed. </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="session-head submission" id="collapse-sess208-head"> <a href="#collapse-sess208" data-toggle="collapse" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseExample"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td"> <div class="collapse-text"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td time"> </div> <div class="td title"> <span><strong>MS09 Computational Models of Tissue Dynamics</strong>, Villa Ciani, Room 005</span> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="td icon"> <div class="collapse-icon"> <div class="spotws-svg arrow-right"> <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" id="Ebene_1" x="0px" y="0px" width="48px" height="48px" viewBox="0 0 48 48" style="enable-background:new 0 0 48 48;" xml:space="preserve" class="spot-svg spot-svg-arrow-right"> <g id="Page-1"> <g id="arrow-left"> <polygon id="Shape-Copy-3" points=