	</script><div class="title">Integrated Physiology in Modelica: HumMod and Physiomodel</div> <div class="table author-items submission-introduction"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td td-label">Presenter:</div> <div class="td"> <div class="authors inline"> <div class="author"> Jiří Kofránek (Charles University, Czech Republic)</span> <script class="pasc-biography-item-json" type="text/template">
		{"id":"msa248","title":"Prof.","bio":"","first_name":"Ji\u0159\u00ed","last_name":"Kofr\u00e1nek","affiliation":"Charles University","country":"Czech Republic","is_presenter":"1"}
	</script></div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="btn btn-primary btn-extra-small show-abstract" title="Abstract">+ Abstract</a> <div class="abstract hidden"> Sophisticated medical training simulators must include models of various physiological subsystems, and also integrate them into a comprehensive whole. One of the largest models of integrated physiological systems called HumMod (http://hummod.org) is implemented as open source by thousands of XML files. Our reimplementation and extension of HumMod 1.6 in the Modelica language called PHYSIOMODEL (http://physiomodel.org), has brought a much clearer and more understandable description of the simulated complex physiological relationships than XML implementation. Modelica is well suited to exactly formalize integrative physiology. Modelica is an equation-based, and object-oriented language for hybrid ordinary differential equations. Almost every physiological term can be defined as a class in this language and can be instantiated as many times as it occurs in the body. Each class has a graphical icon for use in diagrams. These diagrams are self-describing; the Modelica code generated from them is the full representation of the underlying mathematical model. </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="session-head simple"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td"> <div class="collapse-text"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td time"> <span>13:00 - 14:00</span> </div> <div class="td title"> <span><strong>Lunch</strong>, Foyer</span> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="td icon"> <div class="collapse-icon"> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="session-head simple"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td"> <div class="collapse-text"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td time"> <span>14:00 - 16:00</span> </div> <div class="td title"> <span><strong>Minisymposia and Papers Sessio