s in symmetric mode and apply heterogeneousload balancing between hosts and coprocessors, identifyingthe relative load distribution either from on-the-fly runtime measurementsor from a priori exhaustive testing. Both approachesperform better than homogeneous load balancing and better thanusing only the CPUs or only the Xeon Phi coprocessors in nativemode. In all set-ups, however, the absolute speedups are impededby the slow MPI communication between Xeon Phi coprocessors. </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="submission item" data-id="pap134"> <div class="item-warp"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td"> <div class="time">15:00 - 15:30</div> </div> <div class="td"> <div class="submission-body"> <script class="pasc-abstract-item-json" type="text/template">
