	</script></div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="btn btn-primary btn-extra-small show-abstract" title="Abstract">+ Abstract</a> <div class="abstract hidden"> In this work, optimization and performance evaluation of ICCG solver (conjugate gradient iterative method (CG) preconditioned by incomplete Cholesky factorization (IC)) on manycore architectures are investigated, where ICCG solver solves sparse symmetric positive definite (SPD) matrices derived from Poisson’s equation discretized by finite-volume method (FVM). Because ICCG includes operations with data-dependency, such as forward/backward substitutions, and incomplete Cholesky factorization, extraction of parallelism by reordering based on CM-RCM (Cyclic Multicoloring on Reverse Cuthill-Mckee) has been applied. Effects of reordering and format for matrix storage (CRS, SELL, SELL-C-Sigma) are considered. The performance was evaluated on a single socket/node of each of Intel Xeon/Phi (Knights Corner, Knights Landing), Intel Xeon (Broadwell-EP), and NVIDIA Tesla P100 (Pascal). Performance of the ICCG with SELL-C-Sigma on Knights Landing was better than existing methods. </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="submission item" data-id="msa123"> <div class="item-warp"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td"> <div class="time">14:30 - 15:00</div> </div> <div class="td"> <div class="submission-body"> <script class="pasc-abstract-item-json" type="text/template">
