	</script><div class="title">Hybrid OpenMP/MPI Parallelization of the Charge Deposition Step in the Global Gyrokinetic Particle-In-Cell Code ORB5</div> <div class="table author-items submission-introduction"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td td-label">Presenter:</div> <div class="td"> <div class="authors inline"> <div class="author"> Emmanuel Lanti (EPFL, Switzerland)</span> <script class="pasc-biography-item-json" type="text/template">
		{"id":"msa194","title":"Mr.","bio":"","first_name":"Emmanuel","last_name":"Lanti","affiliation":"EPFL","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"1"}
	</script></div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="btn btn-primary btn-extra-small show-abstract" title="Abstract">+ Abstract</a> <a href="/fileadmin/user_upload/pasc17/program/MS28.pdf" target="_blank" class="btn btn-primary btn-extra-small show-pdf" title="Presentation">+ Presentation</a> <div class="abstract hidden"> Gyrokinetic simulations are computationally extremely demanding due to the high dimensionality of the physical phase space and the interplay between plasma particles and electromagnetic fields. It is thus essential to make full use of the available numerical resources to be able to simulate more complex physical problems. With the aim of optimizing the gyrokinetic Particle-In-Cell code ORB5 towards exascale computing, a particle sorting method is implemented to increase data locality. Furthermore, different algorithms are used to improve vectorization, and the MPI parallelization is complemented with OpenMP. More specifically, we shall focus on the particle to grid operations involved in the PIC charge deposition step. The latter is critical to parallelize using a shared memory paradigm due to the scatter operations involved. We will present the different algorithms and parallelization schemes implemented in the ORB5 charge deposition step and how they affect the speedup compared to the base MPI case. </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="submission item" data-id="msa140"> <div class="item-warp"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td"> <div class="time">15:30 - 16:00</div> </div> <div class="td"> <div class="submission-body"> <script class="pasc-abstract-item-json" type="text/template">
		{"submission":{"data":{"id":"msa140","code":"","type":"Minisymposium Presentation","title":"Prediction of the Node to Node Communication Costs of a New Gyrokinetic Code with Toroidal Domain","scientific_track":"","abstract":"Gyrokinetic codes running at large scale play a central role in plasma physics. We apply virtual decompositions of the toroidal domain in three dimensions in addition to domain cloning to existing simulations done with the Orb5 code. We determine the communication volume and the number of communication partners per timestep for every virtual subdomain (node) for the particles and the structured mesh. Thus the scaling properties of a code with the new domain decompositions and unchanged Orb5 numerics are derived for simple models of the computer network and processing units. For a typical simulation with 256 million particles and a mesh of 256x512x256 grid points scaling to the entire Piz Daint should be achieved with the new domain decompositions suggested. The knowledge obtained can be used for the design of new gyrokinetic codes and the design of new supercomputers.","begin_time":"15:30","begin_timestamp":"1522243800","end_time":"16:00","end_timestamp":"1522245600","session_date":"Tuesday, June 27, 2017","room":"Room E"},"authors":{"primary":[{"id":"msa140","title":"Dr.","bio":"","first_name":"Andreas","last_name":"Jocksch","affiliation":"ETH Zurich \/ CSCS","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"1"}],"secondary":[{"id":"msa140","title":"Dr.","bio":"","first_name":"Andreas","last_name":"Jocksch","affiliation":"ETH Zurich \/ CSCS","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"1"},{"id":"msa140","title":"Dr.","bio":"","first_name":"Stephan","last_name":"Brunner","affiliation":"EPFL","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"0"},{"id":"msa140","title":"Dr.","bio":"","first_name":"Claudio","last_name":"Gheller","affiliation":"ETH Zurich \/ CSCS","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"0"},{"id":"msa140","title":"Mr.","bio":"","first_name":"Emmanuel","l