	</script><div class="title">Bayesian Uncertainty Quantification and Propagation for Dissipative Particle Dynamics</div> <div class="table author-items submission-introduction"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td td-label">Presenter:</div> <div class="td"> <div class="authors inline"> <div class="author"> Lina Kulakova (ETH Zurich, Switzerland)</span> <script class="pasc-biography-item-json" type="text/template">
		{"id":"msa258","title":"Ms.","bio":"","first_name":"Lina","last_name":"Kulakova","affiliation":"ETH Zurich","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"1"}
	</script></div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="btn btn-primary btn-extra-small show-abstract" title="Abstract">+ Abstract</a> <div class="abstract hidden"> Large Data, advanced sampling methods and High Performance Computing are changing the landscape of Computational Life Sciences. We integrate these three components in a Bayesian uncertainty quantification and prediction framework. In this talk we show the application of this framework to blood flow models using Dissipative Particle Dynamics (DPD). We calibrate the parameters of the DPD solvent using available data on hydrodynamic correlations. We also quantify uncertainties of the blood models using data on Red Blood Cell (RBC) stretching and its rotation frequency in the shear flow. A computational bottleneck for Bayesian inference is the cost of the DPD simulations. We implement a Neural Network surrogate model which is shown to predict the rotation frequency of a RBC in a shear flow given the model parameters. We compare the obtained DPD/RBC parameters with those used in literature and showcase results from simulations with quantified uncertainties. </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="submission item" data-id="msa265"> <div class="item-warp"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td"> <div class="time">14:30 - 15:00</div> </div> <div class="td"> <div class="submission-body"> <script class="pasc-abstract-item-json" type="text/template">
		{"submission":{"data":{"id":"msa265","code":"","type":"Minisymposium Presentation","title":"Combined Computational and Experimental Study of Cell Deformation in Microfluidic Devices","scientific_track":"","abstract":"We will present a new particle-based cell model and its application to simulations of cell passage through the microfluidic devices. We developed two software implementations of the model targeting multi-GPU and multi-CPU supercomputers. We studied experimentally and computationally three cell groups classified by cell size in three microfluidic devices and obtained good agreement between experimental data and model predictions. Further, we studied the impact of different cell components, such as nucleus and cytoskeleton on cell deformation.","begin_time":"14:30","begin_timestamp":"1522240200","end_time":"15:00","end_timestamp":"1522242000","session_date":"Tuesday, June 27, 2017","room":"Villa Ciani, Room 005"},"authors":{"primary":[{"id":"msa265","title":"Mr.","bio":"","first_name":"Kirill","last_name":"Lykov","affiliation":"Universit\u00e0 della Svizzera italiana","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"1"}],"secondary":[{"id":"msa265","title":"Mr.","bio":"","first_name":"Kirill","last_name":"Lykov","affiliation":"Universit\u00e0 della Svizzera italiana","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"1"},{"id":"msa265","title":"Prof.","bio":"","first_name":"Chwee Teck","last_name":"Lim","affiliation":"National University of Singapore","country":"Singapore","is_presenter":"0"},{"id":"msa265","title":"Ms.","bio":"","first_name":"Yasaman","last_name":"Nematbakhsh","affiliation":"National University of Singapore","country":"Singapore","is_presenter":"0"},{"id":"msa265","title":"Prof.","bio":"","first_name":"Igor","last_name":"Pivkin","affiliation":"Universit\u00e0 della Svizzera italiana","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"0"}]}},"sessionDate":"Tuesday, June 27, 2017","room":"Villa Ciani, Room 005","settings":null}
	</script><div class="title">Combined Computational and Experimental Study of Cell Deformation in Microfluidic Devices</div> <div class="table author-items submission-introduction"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td td-label">Presenter:</div> <div class="td"> <div class="authors inline"> <div class="author"> Kirill Lykov (Università della Svizzera italiana, Switzerland)</span> <script class="pasc-biography-item-json" type="text/template">
