	</script></div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="btn btn-primary btn-extra-small show-abstract" title="Abstract">+ Abstract</a> <div class="abstract hidden"> We will present a new particle-based cell model and its application to simulations of cell passage through the microfluidic devices. We developed two software implementations of the model targeting multi-GPU and multi-CPU supercomputers. We studied experimentally and computationally three cell groups classified by cell size in three microfluidic devices and obtained good agreement between experimental data and model predictions. Further, we studied the impact of different cell components, such as nucleus and cytoskeleton on cell deformation. </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="submission item" data-id="msa264"> <div class="item-warp"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td"> <div class="time">15:00 - 15:30</div> </div> <div class="td"> <div class="submission-body"> <script class="pasc-abstract-item-json" type="text/template">
