		{"submission":{"data":{"id":"post142","code":"","type":"Poster","title":"CHE-01 A Molecular Dynamics Study of the Thermodynamics of Attachment of Saccharides to Halloysite","scientific_track":"Chemistry \u0026 Materials","abstract":"Halloysites are a class of tubular alumino-silicates often integrated within polymeric matrices as mechanical reinforcement or\/and as drug carriers. To maximize the strength of the final material and control drug delivery, it is important to evaluate the polymer-mineral interaction at the interface. Here, Molecular Dynamics simulations have been used to investigate the adsorption of different saccharides on the halloysite surface. By using Umbrella Sampling, we extract the change in free energy related to the attachment of protonated and unprotonated chitosan, chitin and alginate. These saccharides were chosen because of their different functionalities and their importance towards biotechnological applications. The results show that all saccharides can bind to the surface, even though alginate does so when additional cations are present in the solution. By running the free energies calculations at different temperatures, we extracted the enthalpy and entropy of reaction, thereby allowing us to understand the binding driving force.","begin_time":"19:00","begin_timestamp":"1522256400","end_time":"21:00","end_timestamp":"1522263600","session_date":"Tuesday, June 27, 2017","room":"Foyer"},"authors":{"primary":[{"id":"post142","title":"Dr.","bio":"","first_name":"Riccardo","last_name":"Innocenti Malini","affiliation":"Empa","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"1"}],"secondary":[{"id":"post142","title":"Dr.","bio":"","first_name":"Riccardo","last_name":"Innocenti Malini","affiliation":"Empa","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"1"},{"id":"post142","title":"Prof.","bio":"","first_name":"Rene","last_name":"Rossi","affiliation":"Empa","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"0"},{"id":"post142","title":"Dr.","bio":"","first_name":"Fabrizi