	</script><div class="title">CLI-04 GridTools: A C++ Library for Computations on Grids</div> <div class="table author-items submission-introduction"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td td-label">Presenter:</div> <div class="td"> <div class="authors inline"> <div class="author"> Mauro Bianco (ETH Zurich / CSCS, Switzerland)</span> <script class="pasc-biography-item-json" type="text/template">
		{"id":"post144","title":"Dr.","bio":"","first_name":"Mauro","last_name":"Bianco","affiliation":"ETH Zurich \/ CSCS","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"1"}
	</script></div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="fields tr"> <div class="td td-label">Track(s): </div> <div class="td data-multiple"> <div class="field"> <div class="field-name">Climate &amp; Weather</div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="btn btn-primary btn-extra-small show-abstract" title="Abstract">+ Abstract</a> <a href="/fileadmin/user_upload/pasc17/program/post144s2.pdf" target="_blank" class="btn btn-primary btn-extra-small show-pdf" title="Presentation">+ Presentation</a> <div class="abstract hidden"> GridTools is a set of libraries to execute stencil-like computations on a variety of different parallel architectures. The central component of GridTools is the stencil-composition library, which allows high-level composition of multiple stencil applications while the platform specific backends deal with its efficient execution. Other components deal with inter-node communication, boundary conditions and storage infrastructure. The target applications for GridTools are regional weather models (regular grids) as well as global weather and climate simulations (irregular grids). In this poster we describe the software structure and capabilities of the GridTools libraries. Currently supported architectures are clusters of multicore (x86) and multi-GPU nodes. We are currently working on supporting additional platforms, including Xeon Phi, and ARM based machines. </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="submission item" data-id="post135"> <div class="item-warp"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td"> <div class="time">19:00 - 21:00</div> </div> <div class="td"> <div class="submission-body"> <script class="pasc-abstract-item-json" type="text/template">
