		{"submission":{"data":{"id":"post127","code":"","type":"Poster","title":"CSM-01 A Novel and Efficient Compressed Algorithm for Non-Negative Matrix Factorization (NMF)","scientific_track":"Computer Science \u0026 Applied Mathematics","abstract":"Non-negative matrix factorization (NMF) is one of the most popular decomposition techniques for multivariate data. NMF is a core method for many machine learning-related computational problems, such as data compression, feature extraction, word embedding, recommender systems etc. In practice, however, its application is facing challenges in recent years. These challenges stem from the fact that the datasets available are evergrowing in size. For large datasets, NMF algorithm efficiency poses demands on data loading and distribution into and within the available memory and communication between computational nodes. Here we present a novel and efficient compressed NMF algorithm. Our algorithm applies a random compression scheme to drastically reduce the dimensionality of the problem while preserving most of the action of the data matrix and inherently limiting the memory and communication load. As a consequence our algorithm supersedes existing methods in speed but it matches the best non-compressed algorithms in reconstruction precision.","begin_time":"19:00","begin_timestamp":"1522256400","end_time":"21:00","end_timestamp":"1522263600","session_date":"Tuesday, June 27, 2017","room":"Foyer"},"authors":{"primary":[{"id":"post127","title":"Dr.","bio":"","first_name":"Gabriele","last_name":"Torre","affiliation":"FHNW","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"1"}],"secondary":[{"id":"post127","title":"Dr.","bio":"","first_name":"Gabriele","last_name":"Torre","affiliation":"FHNW","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"1"},{"id":"post127","title":"Dr.","bio":"","first_name":"Michael H.","last_name":"Graber","affiliation":"FHNW","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"0"}]},"presentation_file":"post127s2.pdf"},"sessionDate":"Tuesda