	</script><div class="title">CSM-01 A Novel and Efficient Compressed Algorithm for Non-Negative Matrix Factorization (NMF)</div> <div class="table author-items submission-introduction"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td td-label">Presenter:</div> <div class="td"> <div class="authors inline"> <div class="author"> Gabriele Torre (FHNW, Switzerland)</span> <script class="pasc-biography-item-json" type="text/template">
		{"id":"post127","title":"Dr.","bio":"","first_name":"Gabriele","last_name":"Torre","affiliation":"FHNW","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"1"}
	</script></div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="fields tr"> <div class="td td-label">Track(s): </div> <div class="td data-multiple"> <div class="field"> <div class="field-name">Computer Science &amp; Applied Mathematics</div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="btn btn-primary btn-extra-small show-abstract" title="Abstract">+ Abstract</a> <a href="/fileadmin/user_upload/pasc17/program/post127s2.pdf" target="_blank" class="btn btn-primary btn-extra-small show-pdf" title="Presentation">+ Presentation</a> <div class="abstract hidden"> Non-negative matrix factorization (NMF) is one of the most popular decomposition techniques for multivariate data. NMF is a core method for many machine learning-related computational problems, such as data compression, feature extraction, word embedding, recommender systems etc. In practice, however, its application is facing challenges in recent years. These challenges stem from the fact that the datasets available are evergrowing in size. For large datasets, NMF algorithm efficiency poses demands on data loading and distribution into and within the available memory and communication between computational nodes. Here we present a novel and efficient compressed NMF algorithm. Our algorithm applies a random compression scheme to drastically reduce the dimensionality of the problem while preserving most of the action of the data matrix and inherently limiting the memory and communication load. As a consequence our algorithm supersedes existing methods in speed but it matches the best non-compressed algorithms in reconstruction precision. </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="submission item" data-id="post103"> <div class="item-warp"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td"> <div class="time">19:00 - 21:00</div> </div> <div class="td"> <div class="submission-body"> <script class="pasc-abstract-item-json" type="text/template">
		{"submission":{"data":{"id":"post103","code":"","type":"Poster","title":"CSM-02 A Resilient ULFM-MPI-Based PDE Solver: Performance Scaling and Energy Analysis","scientific_track":"Computer Science \u0026 Applied Mathematics","abstract":"We present a resilient task-based domain-decomposition preconditioner for partial differential equations (PDEs) built on top of User Level Fault Mitigation Message Passing Interface (ULFM-MPI). The algorithm reformulates the PDE as a sampling problem, followed by a robust regression-based solution update resilient to silent data corruptions (SDCs). We adopt a server-client model where all state information is held by the servers, and clients only serve as computational units. The task-based nature of the algorithm and the capabilities of ULFM complement each other to support missing tasks, making the application resilient to clients failing. We present weak and strong scaling results showing that even in the presence of faults, scalability tested up to 50k cores is above 90% efficiency. We quantify the variability of weak and strong scaling due to the presence of faults and discuss the interplay between energy and resilience.","begin_time":"19:00","begin_timestamp":"1522256400","end_time":"21:00","end_timestamp":"1522263600","session_date":"Tuesday, June 27, 2017","room":"Foyer"},"authors":{"primary":[{"id":"post103","title":"Dr.","bio":"","first_name":"Karla","last_name":"Morris","affiliation":"Sandia National Laboratories","country":"United States of America","is_presenter":"1"}],"secondary":[{"id":"post103","title":"Dr.","bio":"","first_name":"Karla","last_name":"Morris","affiliation":"Sandia National Laboratories","country":"United States of America","is_presenter":"1"},{"id":"post103","title":"Dr.","bio":"","first_name":"Brandon","last_name":"Cook","affiliation":"Lawrence Berkeley National Laboratory","country":"United States of America","is_presenter":"0"},{"id":"post103","title":"Ms.","bio":"","first_name":"Kathryn","last_na