	</script><div class="title">CSM-03 AV-Flow: A Software Library for Fluid Structure Interaction Problems Based on Variational Transfer Immersed Boundary Method</div> <div class="table author-items submission-introduction"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td td-label">Presenter:</div> <div class="td"> <div class="authors inline"> <div class="author"> Marco Favino (Università della Svizzera italiana, Switzerland)</span> <script class="pasc-biography-item-json" type="text/template">
		{"id":"post121","title":"Dr.","bio":"","first_name":"Marco","last_name":"Favino","affiliation":"Universit\u00e0 della Svizzera italiana","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"1"}
	</script></div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="fields tr"> <div class="td td-label">Track(s): </div> <div class="td data-multiple"> <div class="field"> <div class="field-name">Computer Science &amp; Applied Mathematics</div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="btn btn-primary btn-extra-small show-abstract" title="Abstract">+ Abstract</a> <a href="/fileadmin/user_upload/pasc17/program/post121s2.pdf" target="_blank" class="btn btn-primary btn-extra-small show-pdf" title="Presentation">+ Presentation</a> <div class="abstract hidden"> We present a new approach for Fluid Structure Interaction (FSI) based on the variational transfer immersed boundary method, which has been realized in the software library AV-Flow. To this aim we couple a finite-element code for discretizing the equations of the solid structure with a finite-difference code used for simulating the fluid flow. Since it is known that the use of variational approaches represents an essential ingredient for the stable information transfer between non-matching overlapping meshes, in our framework a pseudo L2 projection approach is adopted to transfer data between the fluid and the solid grid. We provide a description of the complete methodology adopted to solve the FSI problem by including also details about the fluid and the solid solvers. Finally, for validating our methodology, we present results for an FSI benchmarking configuration describing the self induced oscillating deformations of an elastic beam in a flow channel. </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="submission item" data-id="post104"> <div class="item-warp"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td"> <div class="time">19:00 - 21:00</div> </div> <div class="td"> <div class="submission-body"> <script class="pasc-abstract-item-json" type="text/template">
		{"submission":{"data":{"id":"post104","code":"","type":"Poster","title":"CSM-04 Boundary Element Quadrature Schemes for Multi- and Many-Core Architectures","scientific_track":"Computer Science \u0026 Applied Mathematics","abstract":"The presented poster concentrates on an efficient implementation of quadrature routines building the core of the boundary element method (BEM) for solving partial differential equations. We discuss two popular approaches treating the singular integrals specific for BEM, namely their regularization and subsequent four-dimensional tensor Gauss-Legendre scheme and the more challenging semi-analytic quadrature. We focus on manual vectorization of the routines by appropriate refactorization of underlying data structures and the utilization of OpenMP pragmas. The proposed techniques perform well for the standard BEM assembly as well as for the assembly accelerated by the adaptive cross approximation. Numerical experiments have been performed both on multi- and many-core systems including the Knights Landing processors representing the Intel Xeon Phi architecture. The discussed approach is implemented within the BEM4I library developed by the authors at the IT4Innovations National Supercomputing Center.","begin_time":"19:00","begin_timestamp":"1522256400","end_time":"21:00","end_timestamp":"1522263600","session_date":"Tuesday, June 27, 2017","room":"Foyer"},"authors":{"primary":[{"id":"post104","title":"Mr.","bio":"","first_name":"Jan","last_name":"Zapletal","affiliation":"TU Ostrava","country":"Czech Republic","is_presenter":"1"}],"secondary":[{"id":"post104","title":"Mr.","bio":"","first_name":"Jan","last_name":"Zapletal","affiliation":"TU Ostrava","country":"Czech Republic","is_presenter":"1"},{"id":"post104","title":"Mr.","bio":"","first_name":"Lukas","last_name":"Maly","affiliation":"TU Ostrava","country":"Czech Republic","is_presenter":"0"},{"id":"post104","title":"Dr.","bio":"","first_name":"Michal","last_name":"Merta","affiliation":"T