	</script></div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="fields tr"> <div class="td td-label">Track(s): </div> <div class="td data-multiple"> <div class="field"> <div class="field-name">Computer Science &amp; Applied Mathematics</div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="btn btn-primary btn-extra-small show-abstract" title="Abstract">+ Abstract</a> <a href="/fileadmin/user_upload/pasc17/program/post147s2.pdf" target="_blank" class="btn btn-primary btn-extra-small show-pdf" title="Presentation">+ Presentation</a> <div class="abstract hidden"> The human heart presents a challenge to numerical simulations, as it is a complex geometry and it includes deformable soft tissues. We address this challenge by presenting a Fluid-Structure interaction (FSI) approach, based on the immersed boundary (IB) method. Moreover, a semi-automatic procedure to get hybrid three dimensional heart meshes (structured for the fluid, unstructured for the soft tissue), based on the segmentation of patient specific data obtained by computed tomography (CT) scans, is presented. </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="submission item" data-id="post122"> <div class="item-warp"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td"> <div class="time">19:00 - 21:00</div> </div> <div class="td"> <div class="submission-body"> <script class="pasc-abstract-item-json" type="text/template">
