	</script><div class="title">CSM-12 Parallel Immersed Boundary Simulations of Worm-Like Swimmers in the Inertial Flow Regime</div> <div class="table author-items submission-introduction"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td td-label">Presenter:</div> <div class="td"> <div class="authors inline"> <div class="author"> Seyedsaeed Mirazimi (Simon Fraser University, Canada)</span> <script class="pasc-biography-item-json" type="text/template">
		{"id":"post106","title":"Mr.","bio":"","first_name":"Seyedsaeed","last_name":"Mirazimi","affiliation":"Simon Fraser University","country":"Canada","is_presenter":"1"}
	</script></div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="fields tr"> <div class="td td-label">Track(s): </div> <div class="td data-multiple"> <div class="field"> <div class="field-name">Computer Science &amp; Applied Mathematics</div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="btn btn-primary btn-extra-small show-abstract" title="Abstract">+ Abstract</a> <a href="/fileadmin/user_upload/pasc17/program/post106s2.pdf" target="_blank" class="btn btn-primary btn-extra-small show-pdf" title="Presentation">+ Presentation</a> <div class="abstract hidden"> Hydrodynamic interactions in suspensions of swimming organisms (active fluids) has been a topic of recent interest, especially in the study of collective motion of bacteria, spermatozoa and marine worms. To accurately capture the collective behavior of swimmers in both dilute and dense suspensions, it is essential that hydrodynamic interactions be captured. We are most interested in flows at moderate Reynolds numbers in the range from 0.1 to 100, in which both advective and diffusive effects are present and the fluid dynamics obey the Navier-Stokes equations. We employ the immersed boundary method to couple the elastic deformations of a swimming worm with the fluid, which yields a system of coupled integro-differential equations. To solve this system numerically, we employ a parallel immersed boundary algorithm that is implemented in C++. We simulate individual swimmer dynamics and pairwise interactions for worm-like organisms, where both synchronization and mutual attraction of nearby swimmers are observed. </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="submission item" data-id="post156"> <div class="item-warp"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td"> <div class="time">19:00 - 21:00</div> </div> <div class="td"> <div class="submission-body"> <script class="pasc-abstract-item-json" type="text/template">
		{"submission":{"data":{"id":"post156","code":"","type":"Poster","title":"CSM-13 Parallelization of Graph Partitioning using Metis and OpenMP","scientific_track":"Computer Science \u0026 Applied Mathematics","abstract":"Algorithms that find optimal partitions for highly unstructured graphs have a wide range of applications.  These applications include load balancing in super-computers, fill-reducing orderings of sparse matrices and design of very large scale integrated circuits (VLSI).  METIS is a well-known set of serial programs developed by the Karypis Lab designed to solve this problem.  However, METIS was not originally designed to run in multiple processors.  In this project we will use OpenMP (Open Multi-Processing), an API managed by the nonprofit consortium OpenMP Architecture Review Board, to parallelize METIS.  We will then compare the parallelized version with the original METIS to gain an understanding of the performance improvements that can be obtained.","begin_time":"19:00","begin_timestamp":"1522256400","end_time":"21:00","end_timestamp":"1522263600","session_date":"Tuesday, June 27, 2017","room":"Foyer"},"authors":{"primary":[{"id":"post156","title":"Mr.","bio":"","first_name":"Rodrigo","last_name":"Pinto Coelho","affiliation":"Universit\u00e0 della Svizzera italiana","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"1"}],"secondary":[{"id":"post156","title":"Mr.","bio":"","first_name":"Rodrigo","last_name":"Pinto Coelho","affiliation":"Universit\u00e0 della Svizzera italiana","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"1"},{"id":"post156","title":"Mr.","bio":"","first_name":"Radim","last_name":"Janalik","affiliation":"Universit\u00e0 della Svizzera italiana","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"0"},{"id":"post156","title":"Dr.","bio":"","first_name":"Olaf","last_name":"Schenk","affiliation":"Universit\u00e0 della Svizzera italiana","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"0"}]},"presentation_file":"post156s2.pdf"},"sessionDate":"Tuesday, June 27, 2017","room