	</script><div class="title">CSM-15 Shifter: Experiences with High-Performance Containers</div> <div class="table author-items submission-introduction"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td td-label">Presenter:</div> <div class="td"> <div class="authors inline"> <div class="author"> Kean Mariotti (ETH Zurich / CSCS, Switzerland)</span> <script class="pasc-biography-item-json" type="text/template">
		{"id":"post130","title":"Mr.","bio":"","first_name":"Kean","last_name":"Mariotti","affiliation":"ETH Zurich \/ CSCS","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"1"}
	</script></div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="fields tr"> <div class="td td-label">Track(s): </div> <div class="td data-multiple"> <div class="field"> <div class="field-name">Computer Science &amp; Applied Mathematics</div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="btn btn-primary btn-extra-small show-abstract" title="Abstract">+ Abstract</a> <a href="/fileadmin/user_upload/pasc17/program/post130s2.pdf" target="_blank" class="btn btn-primary btn-extra-small show-pdf" title="Presentation">+ Presentation</a> <div class="abstract hidden"> High Performance Computing (HPC) applications have to reliably run across many platforms and environments. Containers are a type of lightweight virtualization technology that attempts to solve this problem by packaging applications and their runtime environments into standard units of software that are: portable, easy to build and deploy, have a small footprint and a low runtime overhead. In this poster, we present a container workflow for HPC applications using two tools: Docker, for building and packaging applications into containers; and Shifter, a container runtime that has been built to fulfill the specific needs of HPC. We will present use cases of building and testing containers on workstations and deploying them on HPC systems, where they take advantage of the available specialized-hardware: fast interconnects and GPU accelerators. We will provide performance results for a variety of scientific applications and discuss how such workflow can aid HPC users. </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="submission item" data-id="post143"> <div class="item-warp"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td"> <div class="time">19:00 - 21:00</div> </div> <div class="td"> <div class="submission-body"> <script class="pasc-abstract-item-json" type="text/template">
		{"submission":{"data":{"id":"post143","code":"","type":"Poster","title":"CSM-16 Solving Large Scale Quadratic Programming Problems with PERMON","scientific_track":"Computer Science \u0026 Applied Mathematics","abstract":"PERMON forms a collection of software libraries exploiting and extending PETSc. The PermonQP module aims to be a general purpose QP solver. It can be used within many application areas where QP problems arise, such as least-squares regression, data fitting, SVM, VRP, and many others. The underlying method is an alternative to more widely used Interior Point Methods. One of its advantages is that it allows very general, possibly implicit (unassembled, matrix-free) constraint and Hessian matrices. It consists in combination of QP transforms, particularly Lagrangian dualization, an outer loop based on augmented Lagrangian (SMALXE), and specific solvers for box-constrained QP. This combination allows solving a general class of QP problems. PermonFLLOP implements the TFETI domain decomposition method. It prepares TFETI-specific objects such as the gluing matrix and kernel basis, and then calls PermonQP to solve the resulting equality-constrained problem with additional inequality constraints in case of contact problems.","begin_time":"19:00","begin_timestamp":"1522256400","end_time":"21:00","end_timestamp":"1522263600","session_date":"Tuesday, June 27, 2017","room":"Foyer"},"authors":{"primary":[{"id":"post143","title":"Dr.","bio":"","first_name":"Vaclav","last_name":"Hapla","affiliation":"IT4Innovations National Supercomputing Center","country":"Czech Republic","is_presenter":"1"}],"secondary":[{"id":"post143","title":"Dr.","bio":"","first_name":"Vaclav","last_name":"Hapla","affiliation":"IT4Innovations National Supercomputing Center","country":"Czech Republic","is_presenter":"1"},{"id":"post143","title":"Dr.","bio":"","first_name":"Martin","last_name":"Cermak","affiliation":"IT4Innovations National Supercomputing Center","country":"Czech Republic","i