	</script><div class="title">EMD-01 Scalable MCMC Algorithm for the Accurate Estimation of Exponential Random Graph Models</div> <div class="table author-items submission-introduction"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td td-label">Presenter:</div> <div class="td"> <div class="authors inline"> <div class="author"> Maksym Byshkin (Università della Svizzera italiana, Switzerland)</span> <script class="pasc-biography-item-json" type="text/template">
		{"id":"post105","title":"Dr.","bio":"","first_name":"Maksym","last_name":"Byshkin","affiliation":"Universit\u00e0 della Svizzera italiana","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"1"}
	</script></div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="fields tr"> <div class="td td-label">Track(s): </div> <div class="td data-multiple"> <div class="field"> <div class="field-name">Emerging Domains in HPC</div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="btn btn-primary btn-extra-small show-abstract" title="Abstract">+ Abstract</a> <div class="abstract hidden"> The increase in the number and size of large network data sets requires novel efficient methods for their analysis. Exponential Random Graph Models (ERGMs) are a general form of probability distribution widely applicable to the analysis of social and other networks. The scope of ERGMs is limited by the fact that existing estimation approaches rely on iterative computational methods that carry out large number of Markov Chain Monte Carlo (MCMC) simulations to draw equilibrium network configurations. Estimation approaches include Bayesian, maximum likelihood and the method of moments. We propose an accurate estimation approach, based on network properties at MCMC equilibrium, and design a simple and efficient algorithm that estimates model parameters several orders of magnitude faster than existing algorithms. *Generous support from the Swiss National Platform of Advanced Scientific Computing (PASC) is gratefully acknowledged. </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="submission item" data-id="post115"> <div class="item-warp"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td"> <div class="time">19:00 - 21:00</div> </div> <div class="td"> <div class="submission-body"> <script class="pasc-abstract-item-json" type="text/template">
		{"submission":{"data":{"id":"post115","code":"","type":"Poster","title":"ENG-01 A Multiscale Model for the Simulation of Sediment Impact Erosion of Metallic Targets","scientific_track":"Engineering","abstract":"Erosion damage in hydraulic turbines is a common problem caused by the impact of small sediments entrained in the fluid. The current state-of-the-art simulations rely on CFD particle tracking coupled with erosion correlations that introduce great uncertainty and lack generality. A novel multiscale model of erosion is presented which avoids the use of correlations by explicitly simulating the sediment impacts. The problem is decoupled into its two dominant scales, each of which is solved using the Finite Volume Particle Method. On the microscale, the erosion rate is calculated by means of multi-particle impact simulations which include all the thermomechanical modeling required in the solid. On the macroscale, the sediment flux and impact condition distributions on the target are modeled through particle tracking in the fluid. Finally, a sequential multiscale algorithm allows reproducing the original coupled problem. The proposed model is validated against experimental data with satisfactory results.","begin_time":"19:00","begin_timestamp":"1522256400","end_time":"21:00","end_timestamp":"1522263600","session_date":"Tuesday, June 27, 2017","room":"Foyer"},"authors":{"primary":[{"id":"post115","title":"Mr.","bio":"","first_name":"Sebasti\u00e1n","last_name":"Leguizam\u00f3n","affiliation":"EPFL","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"1"}],"secondary":[{"id":"post115","title":"Mr.","bio":"","first_name":"Sebasti\u00e1n","last_name":"Leguizam\u00f3n","affiliation":"EPFL","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"1"},{"id":"post115","title":"Mr.","bio":"","first_name":"Siamak","last_name":"Alimirzazadeh","affiliation":"EPFL","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"0"},{"id":"post115","title":"Prof.","bio":"","first_name":"Fran\u00e7ois","last_name":"Avellan","affi