	</script><div class="title">LS-04 Flow Stability and Transition Past an Aortic Valve Using a Hybrid Multicore/Manycore Massively Parallel Navier-Stokes Solver</div> <div class="table author-items submission-introduction"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td td-label">Presenter:</div> <div class="td"> <div class="authors inline"> <div class="author"> Hadi Zolfaghari (University of Bern, Switzerland)</span> <script class="pasc-biography-item-json" type="text/template">
		{"id":"post133","title":"Mr.","bio":"","first_name":"Hadi","last_name":"Zolfaghari","affiliation":"University of Bern","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"1"}
	</script></div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="fields tr"> <div class="td td-label">Track(s): </div> <div class="td data-multiple"> <div class="field"> <div class="field-name">Life Sciences</div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="btn btn-primary btn-extra-small show-abstract" title="Abstract">+ Abstract</a> <a href="/fileadmin/user_upload/pasc17/program/post133s2.pdf" target="_blank" class="btn btn-primary btn-extra-small show-pdf" title="Presentation">+ Presentation</a> <div class="abstract hidden"> A massively-parallel 3D Navier-Stokes solver has been accelerated on the GPUs. The solver is used for heart valve simulations, where Immersed Boundary Method is adopted for coupling the fluid and soft tissue domains. Computationally expensive routines of this solver have been offloaded to the GPGPUs of Cray XC50 supercomputer (Piz Daint). The differential kernels such as Jacobi multigrid smoothers were developed with CUDA C API and then wrapped in FORTRAN for integration in the flow solver. The GPU-accelerated kernels were benchmarked on Fermi and Pascal GPUs, resulting in 5x and 20x speedup, respectively. Briskly on Pascal, 33x speedup was achieved by adopting CUDA multi-process service together with MPI. Finally, we performed extensive numerical simulations for investigating the flow instabilities past the aortic sinus cavity. </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="submission item" data-id="post112"> <div class="item-warp"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td"> <div class="time">19:00 - 21:00</div> </div> <div class="td"> <div class="submission-body"> <script class="pasc-abstract-item-json" type="text/template">
		{"submission":{"data":{"id":"post112","code":"","type":"Poster","title":"LS-05 Focused Diversification of Biomolecules for Drug Discovery by Progress Index-Guided Sampling","scientific_track":"Life Sciences","abstract":"The efficient exploration of relevant areas of phase space represents a major challenge in molecular simulations of biological systems. Enhanced sampling protocols try to address this challenge. Progress index-guided sampling evolves several copies of the system in parallel, and sampling redundancy is eliminated by periodically replacing copies exploring the same regions of phase space with less visited conformations. The discovery of new states is driven by spontaneous fluctuations alone. The reseeding heuristic relies on a representation of the system that can be tuned to obtain focused diversification of specific degrees of freedom. By coupling a molecular dynamics code that is efficient on the single node level to an MPI layer managing the reseeding heuristic, the protocol is able to take full advantage of modern HPC resources. Here, we demonstrate that we achieve the focused diversification of two distinct loops in four bromodomains, which are drug targets in epigenetics research.","begin_time":"19:00","begin_timestamp":"1522256400","end_time":"21:00","end_timestamp":"1522263600","session_date":"Tuesday, June 27, 2017","room":"Foyer"},"authors":{"primary":[{"id":"post112","title":"Mr.","bio":"","first_name":"Cassiano","last_name":"Langini","affiliation":"University of Zurich","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"1"}],"secondary":[{"id":"post112","title":"Mr.","bio":"","first_name":"Cassiano","last_name":"Langini","affiliation":"University of Zurich","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"1"},{"id":"post112","title":"Dr.","bio":"","first_name":"Marco","last_name":"Bacci","affiliation":"University of Zurich","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"0"},{"id":"post112","title":"Prof.","bio":"","first_name":"Amedeo","last_name":"Caflisch","affi