	</script><div class="title">The Swiss Personalized Health Network Data Coordination Center - Enabling Research in Personalized Health by Establishing Interoperability of Health-Related Information</div> <div class="table author-items submission-introduction"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td td-label">Presenter:</div> <div class="td"> <div class="authors inline"> <div class="author"> Torsten Schwede (University of Basel, Switzerland)</span> <script class="pasc-biography-item-json" type="text/template">
		{"id":"msa270","title":"Prof.","bio":"","first_name":"Torsten","last_name":"Schwede","affiliation":"University of Basel","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"1"}
	</script></div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="btn btn-primary btn-extra-small show-abstract" title="Abstract">+ Abstract</a> <div class="abstract hidden"> The Swiss Personalized Health Network (SPHN) initiative aims to bring Switzerland to the forefront of personalized health research by establishing nationwide interoperability of biomedical information. Thanks to advances in life sciences, analytical techniques and information technology, both the quality and quantity of data relevant for biomedical research have been increasing dramatically in recent years. Besides systematic research projects, increasing amounts of data are generated as part of routine clinical care, observational studies, and even by individual citizens monitoring themselves ("quantified self"). The "SPHN Data Coordination Center (DCC)" at the SIB Swiss Institute of Bioinformatics will address the technical and semantic challenges of data interoperability to enable scientists to efficiently use and analyze Swiss health-related data in a meaningful way. The growing amount of detailed information on individuals provides an unprecedented opportunity for advancing biomedical research and answering today’s research questions with respect to precision medicine and human health. </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="submission item" data-id="msa279"> <div class="item-warp"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td"> <div class="time">10:30 - 11:00</div> </div> <div class="td"> <div class="submission-body"> <script class="pasc-abstract-item-json" type="text/template">
