	</script><div class="title">From Big Genomic Data to Molecular Insights</div> <div class="table author-items submission-introduction"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td td-label">Presenter:</div> <div class="td"> <div class="authors inline"> <div class="author"> Gunnar Rätsch (ETH Zurich, Switzerland)</span> <script class="pasc-biography-item-json" type="text/template">
		{"id":"msa279","title":"Prof.","bio":"","first_name":"Gunnar","last_name":"R\u00e4tsch","affiliation":"ETH Zurich","country":"Switzerland","is_presenter":"1"}
	</script></div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="btn btn-primary btn-extra-small show-abstract" title="Abstract">+ Abstract</a> <div class="abstract hidden"> This talk will discuss the technical challenges with respect to two large cancer genome initiatives. Within the International Cancer Genome Consortium, we performed a large collaborative study involving whole genome and RNA-sequencing of 27 types of tumors from about 1,200 donors originating from more than 20 countries. We describe the challenges of distributed, collaborative data analysis under compliance constraints. I will also describe the analysis of about 10,000 samples with whole-exome and RNA sequencing to identify RNA splicing differences that are the result of somatic mutations in tumors. The analysis involved processing about 300TB of raw sequencing data and the association testing using linear mixed models of ca. 200,000 phenotypes against about 50,000 somatic mutations. Most of the analysis was performed using ETH’s Euler and LeonardMed compute systems; the latter is providing sufficient I/O bandwidth to perform such studies. </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="session-head submission" id="collapse-sess194-head"> <a href="#collapse-sess194" data-toggle="collapse" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseExample"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td"> <div class="collapse-text"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td time"> </div> <div class="td title"> <span><strong>MS34 HPC for Large Optimization Problems From Data Analysis</strong>, Room B1</span> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="td icon"> <div class="collapse-icon"> <div class="spotws-svg arrow-right"> <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" id="Ebene_1" x="0px" y="0px" width="48px" height="48px" viewBox="0 0 48 48" style="enable-background:new 0 0 48 48;" xml:space