	</script> </div> </div> </div>	</div> </div> <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="btn btn-primary btn-extra-small show-abstract" title="Abstract">+ Abstract</a> <div class="abstract hidden"> We describe two recently developed numerical linear algebra techniques for accelerating electronic structure calculations. In particular, we discuss the use of the selected inversion algorithm for reducing the cubic scaling of conventional Kohn-Sham density functional theory (KSDFT) based electronic structure calculation to at most quadratic, and show how this method can be implemented efficiently on distributed memory parallel computers. We will also examine the use of polynomial filtering in DGDFT, which is a massively parallel KSDFT solver that uses an adaptive local basis set to discretized the Kohn-Sham equation, and show the benefit of this technique for 3D problems. </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="submission item" data-id="msa104"> <div class="item-warp"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td"> <div class="time">09:30 - 10:00</div> </div> <div class="td"> <div class="submission-body"> <script class="pasc-abstract-item-json" type="text/template">
