	</script> </div> </div> </div>	</div> </div> <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="btn btn-primary btn-extra-small show-abstract" title="Abstract">+ Abstract</a> <div class="abstract hidden"> Sparse matrix computations arise in numerous computational science and engineering applications such as computational nanoelectronics. In order to insure effective use of parallel architectures, one often needs to design afresh sparse matrix primitives and algorithms that are capable of reducing memory references and interprocessor communications. In this presentation, we describe: (i) hybrid parallel algorithms for solving sparse linear systems, and (ii) a parallel algorithm for obtaining a few of the eigenpairs of symmetric generalized eigenvalue problems. Numerical experiments that demonstrate the robustness and parallel scalability of these algorithms are conducted, and comparisons made with established linear system and symmetric eigenvalue problem solvers. </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class="submission item" data-id="msa120"> <div class="item-warp"> <div class="table"> <div class="tr"> <div class="td"> <div class="time">10:00 - 10:30</div> </div> <div class="td"> <div class="submission-body"> <script class="pasc-abstract-item-json" type="text/template">
